01:05:21.309 --> 01:05:23.350
I have a very particular
thought about innovation

01:05:23.350 --> 01:05:24.600
that I want to share with you.

01:05:26.700 --> 01:05:31.840
This is a diagram from a
very famous design consultant

01:05:31.840 --> 01:05:34.460
and how they explain innovation.

01:05:34.460 --> 01:05:39.100
Now, I think I see
where they're going.

01:05:39.100 --> 01:05:42.160
They talk about the business
on one side, technology

01:05:42.160 --> 01:05:44.024
and people.

01:05:44.024 --> 01:05:46.440
And they say, look, innovation
happens in different places

01:05:46.440 --> 01:05:46.940
here.

01:05:46.940 --> 01:05:48.750
Process innovation
occurs between business

01:05:48.750 --> 01:05:49.650
and technology.

01:05:49.650 --> 01:05:51.310
Functional innovation
occurs over here.

01:05:51.310 --> 01:05:53.851
Emotional innovation occurs over
here, like building a brand.

01:05:57.040 --> 01:05:58.920
And then they have
experience innovation.

01:05:58.920 --> 01:06:03.060
And this is this thing
that's very, very special.

01:06:03.060 --> 01:06:04.870
They say yes, when we
combine understanding

01:06:04.870 --> 01:06:08.030
of the business, the
technology, the people.

01:06:08.030 --> 01:06:09.660
Do we build something
that people want?

01:06:09.660 --> 01:06:11.260
Is it able to be built?

01:06:11.260 --> 01:06:13.930
And will it create a business
that can sustain itself?

01:06:13.930 --> 01:06:19.450
Then we have achieved great
experience innovation.

01:06:19.450 --> 01:06:20.630
Now it's not a bad model.

01:06:20.630 --> 01:06:22.088
And it's not untrue
that innovation

01:06:22.088 --> 01:06:23.852
occurs in these places.

01:06:23.852 --> 01:06:26.440
But I think it's
not a useful model.

01:06:26.440 --> 01:06:30.670
I think in that zone here, you
build things that are useful.

01:06:30.670 --> 01:06:31.820
They're useful.

01:06:31.820 --> 01:06:33.770
But they may not be innovative.

01:06:33.770 --> 01:06:35.270
So here's my thing
about innovation.

01:06:40.250 --> 01:06:42.480
There's something out there.

01:06:42.480 --> 01:06:44.650
There's something.

01:06:44.650 --> 01:06:48.390
And you're required
to do something

01:06:48.390 --> 01:06:50.800
and yet you have this
other tension pulling you

01:06:50.800 --> 01:06:53.190
because you desire to
do something else that

01:06:53.190 --> 01:06:54.170
seems in conflict.

01:06:57.290 --> 01:07:01.500
I'm required to create
a nuclear powered car

01:07:01.500 --> 01:07:04.100
but-- I desire to create
a nuclear powered car,

01:07:04.100 --> 01:07:07.550
but I'm required to adhere
to laws of government,

01:07:07.550 --> 01:07:09.240
which is causing
a lot of problems.

01:07:09.240 --> 01:07:20.220
I am required to make an
artificial heart valve

01:07:20.220 --> 01:07:23.260
and I want to make
that but what I realize

01:07:23.260 --> 01:07:26.050
is that there's a problem
because in this requirement,

01:07:26.050 --> 01:07:28.990
I have something that spins
and it creates friction.

01:07:28.990 --> 01:07:32.100
And the friction causes
blood platelets to form

01:07:32.100 --> 01:07:34.640
and causes clotting.

01:07:34.640 --> 01:07:37.086
And I desire to have no clotting
happen even though I have

01:07:37.086 --> 01:07:40.670
this spinning object
in a heart valve.

01:07:40.670 --> 01:07:41.830
Tension.

01:07:41.830 --> 01:07:44.590
I'm required to
pass the class but I

01:07:44.590 --> 01:07:47.185
desire to go out
drinking with my friends.

01:07:47.185 --> 01:07:48.060
These are in tension.

01:07:48.060 --> 01:07:48.560
OK.

01:07:48.560 --> 01:07:54.610
So when you have this and
you start stretching this,

01:07:54.610 --> 01:07:58.440
by resolving this, this is
where innovation occurs.

01:07:58.440 --> 01:08:01.810
Innovation is the result
of resolving your need

01:08:01.810 --> 01:08:07.470
to do something with your
desire of how it can be done.

01:08:07.470 --> 01:08:10.520
The designer's job
is to reconcile

01:08:10.520 --> 01:08:14.100
the seemingly irreconcilable.

01:08:14.100 --> 01:08:17.290
The designer's job
is to reconcile

01:08:17.290 --> 01:08:18.903
the seemingly irreconcilable.

01:08:21.710 --> 01:08:23.187
It's not that you can't do it.

01:08:23.187 --> 01:08:24.520
Maybe you think you can't do it.

01:08:24.520 --> 01:08:26.396
It appears that you can't do it.

01:08:26.396 --> 01:08:28.812
But you gotta think about it
differently or think about it

01:08:28.812 --> 01:08:29.560
from a new angle.

01:08:29.560 --> 01:08:32.297
Or get some new
information to resolve

01:08:32.297 --> 01:08:33.505
the seemingly irreconcilable.

01:08:33.505 --> 01:08:37.109
And that is what your
job is your whole lives

01:08:37.109 --> 01:08:40.779
is to try to figure out the
solution to these problems.

01:08:40.779 --> 01:08:43.020
If they were obvious,
people would just do them.

01:08:43.020 --> 01:08:44.603
But when they're not
obvious, and they

01:08:44.603 --> 01:08:46.890
cause this tension,
this pain, this

01:08:46.890 --> 01:08:48.926
is where the innovation occurs.

01:08:48.926 --> 01:08:50.550
And where you get
people who do things.

01:08:50.550 --> 01:08:58.229
Like a company called Levatronix
who took that spinning thing.

01:08:58.229 --> 01:09:00.350
And they said, well,
we know if they're

01:09:00.350 --> 01:09:02.010
touching it causes friction.

01:09:02.010 --> 01:09:04.540
Instead, they used
magnets to levitate it

01:09:04.540 --> 01:09:07.149
so there's no friction at
all inside of a heart valve.

01:09:10.365 --> 01:09:12.656
